title: Owen Davidson, Australian master of doubles tennis, dies at 79
description: Eight of his major titles came with Billie Jean King, with whom he formed a formidable mixed doubles partnership in the 1960s and ’70s.

title: Hitler’s voice plays on Austrian train intercom in disturbing episode
description: The sabotage occurred on a train headed toward Vienna on Sunday. Police say they have identified two perpetrators, who gained access to the intercom system.

title: Zelensky toured Europe seeking new weapons. Here’s what he came home with.
description: Volodymyr Zelensky secured new commitments during visits to Britain, France and Germany that came as Ukraine gears up for a counteroffensive.

title: In photos: The scene in New Zealand after hostel fire kills at least six people
description: At least six people are dead and 11 unaccounted for after a fire broke out overnight at a multistory hostel in New Zealand’s capital, in what fire officials are describing as their “worst nightmare” and a once-in-a-decade event.

title: Ukraine intercepts missiles as Russia steps up strikes on Kyiv
description: Russia fired a fearsome overnight barrage of missiles at Kyiv but Ukrainian officials claimed a perfect interception rate using air defenses bolstered by the West.

title: German court convicts five men for $100 million jewel heist in 2019
description: It was one of Europe’s most daring jewel heists when members of the Remmo clan broke into the Green Vault museum at Dresden’s Royal Palace in a smash-and-grab job.

title: Move over, U.S. dollar. China wants to make the yuan the global currency.
description: Economic crises and Western sanctions against Russia are helping China realize its goal of turning the yuan into an international currency for trade deals.

title: Beijing LGBT Center closes its doors, a blow for diversity in China
description: The move coincided with a new milestone for same-sex couples in Taiwan - they can now adopt - and underscored the lack of progress on LGBTQ issues in China.

title: Ukraine live briefing: Early-morning attack on Kyiv injures 3
description: The Kyiv attack was “exceptional” in its intensity, the city military administration said, and included drones, cruise missiles and possibly ballistic missiles.

title: Erdogan scores win through culture wars and soft authoritarianism
description: The Turkish president is poised to return to power, using a political template that illiberal parties are following around the world.
